President Obama and his wife, Michelle, congratulate Pope Francis on becoming the new Pope. They praise him as a champion for the poor and vulnerable, and as someone who embodies the message of love and compassion. They also highlight the significance of him being the first Pope from the Americas and express their joy alongside millions of Hispanic Americans. President Obama expresses his desire to work with Pope Francis to promote peace, security, and dignity for all people, regardless of their faith. They join people worldwide in offering prayers for the Holy Father as he leads the Catholic Church.